channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Why won't Pennsylvania voters have results on Election Night?
item.description: Pennsylvania Secretary of State Al Schmidt said voters should not expect results on the night of Nov. 5 in a bid to head off repeated 2020 controversy.

item.title: Kennedy puts fresh spin on Harris-Trump showdown in battleground states
item.description: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. struck at the heart of Vice President Kamala Harris' claim that she would protect democracy and freedom when he quit the presidential race and threw his support behind the Republican nominee.

item.title: Salzburg Journal
item.description: Sights and sounds in Mozart’s town.

item.title: Lawmakers: Big Pharma Might Be Cashing In On Experiments On Chinese Slaves
item.description: U.S. companies 'could be unintentionally profiting from the data derived from clinical trials during which the CCP forced victim patients to participate.'

item.title: Minnesotan commutes out of state for 'right to work' after business closed under Walz's COVID-era rules
item.description: Minnesota resident Lisa Zarza commutes two hours a day to work in Wisconsin after losing her businesses under Gov. Tim Walz's COIVD-era policies.

item.title: Sen. Hawley offers a prayer of thanksgiving for Trump
item.description: A Republican senator from Missouri has offered a prayer for former President Donald Trump. That would be Sen. Josh Hawley, and here is what he has to say: "Our Lord has his arms around President Trump," Mr. Hawley said in campaign outreach shared with Inside the Beltway.

item.title: Gouging: Letting Prices Work
item.description: The week of August 19, 2024: The Good Gouger, fiscal policy, China, and much, much, more.

item.title: The Money-Printing That Made Millennials Wealthy Can Bankrupt Them Too
item.description: The Federal Reserve should move as far away as possible from the money-printing policies that have defined the last two decades.

item.title: Walz faced another accusation of misrepresentation in unearthed, blistering letter: 'Remove any reference'
item.description: An unearthed 2006 letter from the Nebraska Chamber of Commerce to then-congressional candidate Tim Walz accused him of misrepresenting an award he won.

item.title: Trump doubles down on tariffs, defies economist naysayers
item.description: Trump had some major successes with tariffs as president and now he's back for more, saying up to 20% tariffs would be justifiable retaliation for unfair practices by America's trading partners.

item.title: Two Publications That Might as Well Be Run by the DNC
item.description: Something weird is happening at Politico and Axios .

item.title: RFK Jr. Eviscerates Democratic Party For ‘Palace Coup’ Harris Nomination
item.description: "How are people to choose when they don't know whom they are choosing? And how can this look to the rest of the world?" Kennedy asked.

item.title: Who is Kamala Harris' 'combative Marxist economist' father, Donald J. Harris?
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' economist father has largely stayed out of the public spotlight, overwhelmingly refraining from discussing his daughter publicly.

item.title: Vance defends Trump's tariffs, denies they cost consumers
item.description: Sen. J.D. Vance defended former President Donald Trump's tariff policy, saying it penalizes importers who undercut American workers, including with "slave labor," not consumers.

item.title: Turning Failure into Tiramisu
item.description: Flat cream puffs can be salvaged by turning them into a non-traditional but delicious tiramisu.

item.title: RFK Jr. Calls Out Media-Government Censorship Complex
item.description: Robert F. Kennedy, Jr., detailed how the media-government censorship complex targeted his campaign in a speech Friday, announcing he would suspend his efforts and endorse former President Donald Trump.

item.title: Harris' push for electric vehicles suffers another blow after automaker backtracks: 'Unwanted and unworkable'
item.description: Ford is backing away from rolling out electric vehicles in favor of hybrid options, indicating more defeats to Harris-backed electric vehicle initiatives.

item.title: Trump would veto legislation establishing a federal abortion ban, Vance says
item.description: Republican vice presidential candidate JD Vance says Donald Trump would not support a national abortion ban if elected president and would veto such legislation if it landed on his desk.

item.title: A Willfully Misguided Plan for Conciliation with Iran
item.description: A figure known for lobbying on behalf of the Islamic Republic has some strange proposals that just happen to benefit that regime.

item.title: RFK Jr. Trashes Estrogenic Seed Oils In Trump Endorsement Speech
item.description: Kennedy explained Americans are getting sick from a toxic food supply saturated with hyper-processed edibles laden with seed oils.
